**QUALITY OVER QUANTITY**<br>
<br>
TO RECEIVE COMPETITOR'S PRICES, ATTENDEES MUST BRING IN LIGATURE FROM COMPETITOR'S WHEN REGISTERING FOR CLASSES.<br>
<br>
<br>
ATTENTION!!! ATTENTION!!!!!<br>
REFER 1 FRIEND OR FAMILY MEMBER AND THEIR 40 HOUR SECURITY AND CCL TRAINING IS FREE!!!!!!<br>
<br>
<br>
We offer many courses from Security Training to Concealed Carry.<br>
For more Information, please visit the site or contact the office. Thank you!!<br>
www.ptcsecurity.com <br>
Phone Number: (773)445-8566<br>
<br>
"Preparation Through Proper Training"<br>
<br>
Train to be a "Security Professional"<br>
<br>
20-Hour Basic Security<br>
<br>
(Unarmed Security Officer Certification Course)<br>
<br>
<br>
This course meets the requirements of The Department of Professional Regulation<br>
as outlined in the Detective Act. <br>
<br>
It covers security fundamentals for new officers <br>
and provides a review for experienced employees who want to<br>
earn state certification in this course. <br>
<br>
Student will received a PERC<br>
(Permanent Employee Registration Card) which is needed for employment<br>
with private security agencies.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Topics Include:<br>
<br>
Security Officer Code of Ethics<br>
<br>
Public Relations, Human Relation and Civil Rights<br>
<br>
Illinois Criminal Code (related to protection of person and property)<br>
<br>
Fire and Accident Prevention; Fire Safety<br>
<br>
Patrol Procedures<br>
<br>
Liability Issues<br>
<br>
Use of Force<br>
<br>
Arrest and Control Techniques<br>
<br>
Laws (regarding arrest, search and seizure)<br>
<br>
Report Writing and Service Process<br>
<br>
The Law on Private Security/Reporting to Law Enforcement Agencies<br>
<br>
Course Fee: $60.00<br>
<br>
<br>
Important Notice!<br>
<br>
PTC Now Offers Utah and Florida<br>
<br>
"Concealed Carry Permits"!!<br>
<br>
WE NOW OFFER<br>
<br>
State of Illinois "Conceal Carry Course"!!<br>
<br>
<br>
20-Hour Fire Arms<br>
<br>
(Armed Security Officer Certification Course)<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Armed officers in Illinois need 40 hours of instruction in order to be certified by the department of professional regulation to carry a firearm in the line of duty.<br>
<br>
After completing 20 hour basic course student enrolls in a 20 hour firearm class to become state certified. Class room instruction is followed by a written test, firing range practice and final qualification.<br>
<br>
A current Illinois Firearm Owner's Identification card (FOID) is a prerequisite to receiving firearm training at PTC. Your FOID card must be presented to the instructor at the beginning of the first day of class. Out of state student are exempt from this requirement. (Attendees must be 21 years or older for this course).<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Topics include:<br>
<br>
Legal use of firearm<br>
<br>
Ethic of firearm use<br>
<br>
Firearm safety and maintenance<br>
<br>
Search /seizure / arrest procedure while armed<br>
<br>
Liability while armed<br>
<br>
Use of deadly force<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
20-hour firearm Course Fee: $100.00<br>
<br>
40-hour full price: $160.00<br>
<br>
Revolver $100.00/Semi-Upgrade $70.00 when taken with firearm course.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Semi-Automatic Upgrade.................... $100.00<br>
<br>
Shotgun Upgrade................................. $125.00 <br>
<br>
Assault Rifle Upgrade ..................... $135.00<br>
<br>
Attention!<br>
<br>
<br>
Range is every Saturday at 12 Noon to 2 pm.<br>
<br>
Range Fee and Ammunition is not included.<br>
<br>
Range Fee will be no more than $50.00<br>
<br>
Re-qualification of Revolver, Semi Automatic<br>
<br>
Shotgun and Rifle - $60.00 per weapon<br>
<br>
Students must have FOID CARD<br>
<br>
Also offering Revolver/ Semi-Automatic/ Shot Gun/ Rifle upgrades for $100.00 per weapon in conjunction with the 40 hour security course.<br>
<br>
A $100.00 fee will apply to attendees not currently enrolled in a course and looking to upgrade their current weapon statue.<br>
<br>
The department of professional regulation requires a $55.00 registration fee to be license as a security officer in the State of Illinois.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Specialized Courses:<br>
Defensive Tactics<br>
OC Spray<br>
Expandable Baton<br>
Handcuffing &amp; Subject control<br>
Weapon retention &amp; disarming<br>
Automated Training System<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Defensive tactic<br>
<br>
This course is designed to provide basic or advance training for individuals seeking to gain hands on knowledge and experience. Attendees will learn several methods of movement to a position of advantage. How to properly escort, control and stabilize a compliant or non-complaint subject. Students will learn to deflect and attack through instinctive (one and two hand) blocking technique. These defensive maneuvers are designed to neutralize the attack (not the attacker). However, when you perform purely protective techniques, you will have to resort to more active defensive means. You will learn counter attacking skill, such as the punch, edged fist, palm-heel strike, knee strike, front kick, and many more.<br>
(1) 4 hour course - 2 yr certification $ 75.00<br>
(2) 8 hour course -4 yr certification $150.00<br>
<br>
OC spray<br>
<br>
The Oleoresin Capsicum course is designed to provide the individual with basic instruction in the proper and legal parameters of OC spray. In this course attendees will learn how, why and when to use state-of -the art concept such as: drawing technique and proper defensive stance, patterns of movement while using aerosol spraying technique, multiple opponent defense, use of cover system defense against moving attacks, disengagement ground defense and where an OC product can fit into the use of force module. <br>
<br>
(1) 4 hour course - 2 yr certification $ 75.00<br>
(2) 8 hour course - 4 yr certification $ 150.00 <br>
<br>
Expandable baton<br>
<br>
This course is designed to teach the individual the Baton Nomenclature stance , patterns of movement, baton grip, baton methods of carry, baton draws, baton two-handed blocks, baton counter strike, and baton retention. Batons are only an artificial extension of the individuals own body. Training links the mind through the baton. <br>
<br>
(1) 4-hour course - 2 yr certification $ 75.00<br>
(2) 8-hour course - 4 yr certification $ 150.00 <br>
<br>
Handcuffing &amp; subject control<br>
<br>
This course is designed to cover the objectives of handcuffing programs, identify the Nomenclature of handcuffs, handcuffing complaint and non-complaint subject, handcuffing in the prone position, use of contact cover, removing handcuffs safely, reduction of injury to the Officer/Subject, reduce liability and increase confidence. <br>
<br>
(1) 4 hour course - 2 yr certification $ 75.00<br>
(2) 8 hour course -4 yr certification $ 150.00 <br>
<br>
Weapon retention &amp; disarming<br>
<br>
This course is designed to teach individuals how to retain their weapon when under attack through a use of series of easy to learn techniques. Close up defensive tactics positions will be explored and practiced in retention of weapons both when holstered and drawn. You will also learn ways to keep your adversary from taking your weapon and possibly using it on you. <br>
<br>
(1) 4 hour course -2 yr certification $ 75.00<br>
(2) 8 hour course - 4 yr certification $ 150.00 <br>
<br>
Firearm simulation training<br>
<br>
This course is designed to teach attendees various shoot and don't shoot scenarios while enhancing individuals shooting skills. <br>
<br>
(1) 4-hour course - 2 yr certification $ 75.00<br>
(2) 8-hour course - 4 yr certification $ 150.00 <br>
<br>
<br>
Executive Protection- $150.00<br>
<br>
Private Investigator- $150.00<br>
<br>
Homeland Security- $150.00<br>
<br>
    </section>

